TopicTitle: I came back and it crashes...

Articles.Content:
Well hello J, 

Sadly you have to make sure that every mod is up to date. Remove all the other mods. It can be done easily by creating a new game (latest version), install all the mods you want, also the right version. If the mod isn't playable with the current ksp you can basically consider two things: 1) skip the mod. 2) if you really want the mod, search for alternative or instal a previous install of ksp. 

Once the new game is setup, you can either copy the save folder to the new one, or make the old game exactly as the new one.  The first option seems the most reasonable.
